    <section id="why" class="section">
        <div class="section-header">
            <div class="section-number">01 — Foundation</div>
            <h2 class="section-title">Why Entrepreneurship Matters</h2>
            <p class="section-slogan">"Building businesses that serve, innovate, and empower"</p>
        </div>

        <div class="impact-grid">
            <div class="impact-card">
                <div class="impact-icon">
                    <i class="fas fa-briefcase"></i>
                </div>
                <h3 class="impact-title">Job Creation & Economic Growth</h3>
                <p class="impact-description">
                    Entrepreneurs are the primary engines of employment, creating opportunities 
                    where none existed before. Every successful venture multiplies its impact through 
                    jobs, supplier relationships, and community economic development.
                </p>
                <div class="impact-example">
                    <strong>Example:</strong> A local restaurant doesn't just employ cooks and servers—it creates 
                    demand for farmers, suppliers, marketers, and supporting service providers, 
                    generating a ripple effect throughout the local economy.
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="impact-card">
                <div class="impact-icon">
                    <i class="fas fa-flask"></i>
                </div>
                <h3 class="impact-title">Innovation & Problem Solving</h3>
                <p class="impact-description">
                    Entrepreneurship transforms challenges into opportunities. By identifying gaps 
                    in the market and unmet needs in society, entrepreneurs develop creative solutions 
                    that improve quality of life and drive progress forward.
                </p>
                <div class="impact-example">
                    <strong>Example:</strong> An accounting firm that provides scholarships doesn't just offer 
                    financial services—it removes barriers to education, cultivates future talent, 
                    and strengthens the entire profession.
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="impact-card">
                <div class="impact-icon">
                    <i class="fas fa-globe-americas"></i>
                </div>
                <h3 class="impact-title">Community Development & Social Impact</h3>
                <p class="impact-description">
                    Beyond profit, entrepreneurship builds community resilience. Socially-conscious 
                    businesses address local needs, preserve cultural identity, and create shared 
                    prosperity that uplifts entire neighborhoods.
                </p>
                <div class="impact-example">
                    <strong>Example:</strong> A sustainable farm enterprise provides fresh, healthy food while 
                    teaching agricultural practices, preserving land, and creating a model for 
                    environmental stewardship that inspires others.
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="impact-card">
                <div class="impact-icon">
                    <i class="fas fa-bolt"></i>
                </div>
                <h3 class="impact-title">Driving Systemic Change</h3>
                <p class="impact-description">
                    Entrepreneurs challenge the status quo and demonstrate better ways of operating. 
                    Through innovation and persistence, they shift industries, influence policy, 
                    and prove that business can be a force for good.
                </p>
                <div class="impact-example">
                    <strong>Example:</strong> By integrating ethical practices from day one, entrepreneurs show 
                    that profitability and social responsibility are not opposing forces but 
                    complementary values that strengthen both business and community.
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="vision-statement">
            <h3 class="vision-title">Entrepreneurship as Responsibility</h3>
            <p class="vision-content">
                To build a business is to accept responsibility—not just for profit and growth, 
                but for the people whose lives we touch, the communities we serve, and the future 
                we help shape. True entrepreneurship recognizes that sustainable success comes from 
                creating value for all stakeholders, not extracting it for the few.
            </p>
        </div>
    </section>
<!-- Page 2: Core Competencies -->
